  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb4\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bae\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0b8e\u0ba9 \u0b89\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Suspicious death of Khandakadu Rehabilitation Center inmate confirmed as murder",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Polonnaruwa \u2013 The suspicious death of an inmate of Kantakadu Rehabilitation Center under Welikanda Police Division has been confirmed as murder. At the Polonnaruwa Hospital, on the body of the said prisoner, according to the order of Polonnaruwa Justice Fatima Minha, special forensic expert UL. This matter has been revealed today (5) in the post-mortem conducted by Sunaga Perera.",
        "It has been revealed through the postmortem report that the said prisoner was attacked with a blunt weapon and as a result of which the prisoner has injuries all over the internal part of the body and the death occurred due to the resulting conditions.",
        "However, in connection with this incident, four soldiers who acted as advisers to the station have been arrested. Welikanda police have arrested two army and two air force personnel in connection with the suspicious death of a 35-year-old prisoner from Padulai-Hali Ela-Temotara area.",
        "According to the statement of the four persons, the police have also seized the wire and bamboo sticks believed to have been used to attack the prisoner.",
        "Among those arrested were 35-year-old from Kottapitiya and 36-year-old from Nawalapitiya, Air Force sergeant-rank officers who were working as consultants at Kantagadu Rehabilitation Centre. Police said that one of the arrested military officers is a stop sergeant aged 39 years from Kalnewa area and the other is a sergeant grade officer aged 37 years from Hurikaswewa.",
        "The suspects were produced before Polonnaruwa Justice Fatima Minha on charges of assault and murder on the 2nd. The judge ordered them to be remanded until the 14th.",
        "Further investigations regarding the incident were carried out by a team under the supervision of Polonnaruwa Senior Police Inspector Oshan Hewavidharana under Welikanda Police Officer-in-Charge Chief Inspector of Police Samantha Ratnayake and Deputy Inspector General of Police Sumathiratne of the Criminal Division."
      ],
